title: Palo Alto Networks lifts earnings guidance as it pursues profitable growth
description: Palo Alto Networks is emphasizing profitability while still adding top-line growth through acquisitions under CEO Nikesh Arora.

title: Starbucks is launching olive oil-infused coffee in Italy, plans U.S. release this spring
description: CEO Howard Schultz teased the release on Starbucks' earnings call, calling it "alchemy" and a "game-changer."

title: The wedding boom is winding down but inflation is still driving up the cost to say 'I do'
description: The average cost of a 2023 wedding is expected to be $29,000 as vendors say inflation is forcing them to raise their prices, according to data from Zola.

title: Amazon employees push CEO Andy Jassy to drop return-to-office mandate
description: Amazon tech workers created an internal petition and Slack channel to share their grievances about the return to work mandate.

title: Facebook and Instagram could have 12 million paying subscribers by early 2024, says BofA
description: A Bank of America (BoFA) research note estimates that Meta's Verified subscription service could generate $1.7 billion "in high-margin revenue in 2024."

title: Elon Musk's lawyer asks court to throw out 'Twitter sitter' deal with SEC
description: Elon Musk's lawyer has asked an appeals court to throw out his 2018 deal with the SEC in light of his recent victory in a securities fraud trial.

title: Goldman-backed battery firm Northvolt earmarks next quarter for U.S. factory announcement
description: The Swedish company has been reevaluating some of its investment decisions in light of the U.S. Inflation Reduction Act.

title: Why it's so hard to build new electrical transmission lines in the U.S.
description: Building transmission lines in the U.S. is a slow process with many stakeholders, and the delays are holding back the country's clean energy transition.

title: Microsoft will bring Xbox games to Nvidia's cloud gaming service
description: Microsoft proposed its $69 billion acquisition of Activision Blizzard in January 2022 but has since faced pushback from regulators over antitrust concerns.

title: Biden speaks in Poland about Russia's war in Ukraine, days before one-year anniversary of invasion
description: Biden's speech in Poland follows a surprise visit to Kyiv, days before the one-year mark since Russia invaded Ukraine.

title: Energy company announces world first as its tidal power project hits major milestone
description: The firm described the news as a "significant milestone in delivering tidal stream power at scale."

title: 'They started the war': Russia's Putin blames West and Ukraine for provoking conflict
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin on Tuesday used a widely-watched speech to deny responsibility for the war in Ukraine and lash out at his adversaries.

title: Mining giant BHP says China and India growth will buoy demand despite profit drop
description: Australian mining giant BHP is optimistic China and India's growth will boost commodity demand, even as the company reported a steep drop in half-year profits.

title: Canada trade minister says trade talks with Taiwan are part of a larger Indo-Pacific strategy
description: Canada's decision to enter formal bilateral trade talks with Taiwan is part of a broader strategy for the Indo-Pacific region, says Canada's minister of international trade.

title: CNBC Daily Open: The Fed wants inflation at 2%. But the economy might be fine with higher inflation
description: The 2% inflation target has been repeated so often by central bankers that it seems crucial to a healthy economy. That assumption may be wrong.

title: Walmart will report holiday-quarter earnings before the bell — here's what to expect
description: Walmart will likely share its outlook for the year ahead, too.

title: HSBC reports fourth-quarter pre-tax profit of $5.2 billion, beating estimates
description: Analyst estimates compiled by the bank had expected a jump of 87% to $4.97 billion.

title: Singapore's digital banks dangle incentives to win new customers — is it sustainable?
description: Digital retail banks in Singapore are pulling out all stops to win new customers, but industry observers question if it's sustainable in the long term.
